Prioritize js over coffee for concat order

- in the strange case that someone has coffeescript _and_ javascript in 
the same project, but the angular module is defined in javascript the
current concat order would cause specs to fail as it added coffee output
prior to js.

- this also adds a note to the readme clarifying this point

Merge pull request #1 from dennisburton/master

Add angular-mocks to spec/helpers

Makes things explicit for dependency injection

Angular likes this way of configuration so that it knows how to inject
the right dependencies even in minified code. Makes sense given uglify
mangles function arguments, but not strings.

Merge pull request #14 from Foxandxss/patch-1

Let npm update protractor with new versions

Let npm update protractor with new versions

I think that protractor is one of those dependencies that doesn't hurt to have at the last version because it is just in its early stages with a lot of bugs (@searls knows what I am talking about :P).

TL;DR; I think that having protractor in the last version doesn't hurt. Feel free to change it to ~0.10.0 or what you want :)
